                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190915-111-off608 t18190915-111-crimeloc611"></join>, in the parish of St. Andrew. On the 1st of September, this coat, which cost me 50 s., hung in my shop. I was at dinner in the parlour, and saw the prisoner go out of the door with it. I followed, and secured him about ten yards from the door with it under his jacket. It has my name in the sleeve. He was sober.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was insensible.</p>
